swapDispute(address,address,address,uint.details: Any collateral the contract has will be used before anything is purchased on Uniswap.

params.deadline: abort the trade and dispute if the transaction is mined after this timestamp.*
params.financialContract: address of the financial contract on which the liquidation is occurring.
params.liquidationId: index of the liquidation for the given sponsor.
params.maxReserveTokenSpent: maximum number of reserve tokens to spend in the trade. Bounds slippage.
params.reserveCurrency: address of the token to swap for collateral. This is the common currency held by the DSProxy.
params.sponsor: address of the sponsor who's liquidation is disputed.
params.uniswapRouter: address of the uniswap router used to facilitate trades.

swapDispute(address,address,address,uint.notice: Swaps required amount of reserve currency to collateral currency which is then used to dispute a liquidation.

userdoc.notice: Helper contract to enable a disputer to hold one reserver currency and dispute against any number of financial contracts. Is assumed to be called by a DSProxy which holds reserve currency.
